Abstract: The paper probes into the basic question of what individuals seek from working. Results from a representative sample of the labor force in seven countries (n = 8192) showed that the two most dominant work goals are &ldquo;interesting work&rdquo; and &ldquo;good pay.&rdquo; These were consistent internationally, across different organizational levels, between the genders and among different age categories.&copy; 1990 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1990) 21, 75&ndash;93
